In C#, you can use the `params` keyword to define a method that takes a variable number of arguments. This allows you to create a function that can accept an undetermined number of arguments of the same type. The `params` parameter must be the last parameter in the method's parameter list.

Here is an example of how you can define a function that takes an undetermined number of arguments in C#:

```csharp
using System;

